# GAMedical Project Documentation (Simple Version)

## 1) What this project does

This project compares two AI models that classify medical images:

- A **Baseline CNN** (regular image AI model)
- A **GA-CNN** (Geometry-Aware CNN using Clifford Algebra ideas)

In simple terms:
- The baseline model looks at pixel patterns in the usual way.
- The GA-CNN tries to keep more information about image structure (shape/orientation relationships) when learning.

The current experiment uses the **PathMNIST** dataset and reports:
- Accuracy and quality scores
- Robustness tests (rotation, blur, brightness, noise)
- Model size and parameter efficiency

---

## 2) Why this matters

Medical images can change because of:
- camera angle
- brightness/lighting
- noise
- blur

A strong model should still perform well when these changes happen.  
This project checks whether geometry-aware learning can improve that.

---

## 3) Quick results snapshot

From `results/ga_cnn_results.json` and `results/results_summary.json`:

- **Baseline CNN test accuracy**: ~80.78%
- **GA-CNN test accuracy**: ~81.09%
- **Accuracy gain (GA-CNN - Baseline)**: ~+0.31%

Other notes:
- GA-CNN has slightly better AUC
- Baseline has slightly better weighted/macro F1 in this run
- GA-CNN is much stronger under image rotation
- Baseline has better blur robustness in this run

So the result is **mixed but promising**: GA-CNN gains some robustness/accuracy, with trade-offs.

---

## 4) Project files (important ones)

- `GAMedical_Complete.ipynb`  
  Full notebook with the end-to-end experiment workflow.

- `clifford_layers.py`  
  Geometry-aware building blocks (encoding + Clifford-style convolution and attention).

- `ga_cnn_models.py`  
  Model definitions:
  - `BaselineCNNRGB`
  - `GeometricAlgebraCNN`
  - `GeometricAlgebraCNNAdvanced`

- `advanced_metrics.py`  
  Extra evaluation tools:
  - Accuracy/F1/AUC tracking
  - Robustness testing (rotation, illumination, blur, noise)
  - Parameter efficiency comparison

- `results/ga_cnn_results.json`  
  Detailed experiment outputs and robustness scores.

- `results/results_summary.json`  
  Short summary of core metrics.

